    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/applicability",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "VAD hemolysis CFD applicability domain",
      "description": "Applicable to single-stage centrifugal blood pumps with impeller diameters between 30 mm and 60 mm, operating at rotational speeds between 2000 and 6000 RPM, with blood-analogue working fluid (viscosity 3.5 ± 0.5 mPa·s, density 1050 ± 10 kg/m³). Model is not applicable to axial-flow pumps, pulsatile assist devices, or operating conditions outside the validated flow-speed envelope. Hemolysis correlation (modified power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger) is valid for exposure times 1–700 ms and shear stresses 10–400 Pa."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "VAD operating envelope — flow, speed, and pressure bounds",
      "description": "Validated operating envelope spans five flow-speed operating points: flow rates 2–8 L/min (step 1.5 L/min), rotational speeds 2500–5000 RPM (step 500 RPM), inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg. Fluid temperature 37 ± 1 °C. Geometric tolerances on pump housing ±0.05 mm CNC. All CFD runs constrained to Reynolds numbers 3000–35 000 (turbulent regime, k-ω SST closure). Hematocrit range 35–45%."
    }
  },
