      },
      "rationale": "Traceability matrix (TM-COU2-v1.2) maps velocity field → shear stress distribution → hemolysis scalar accumulation → NIH. Velocity and WSS are intermediate QoIs that directly drive the hemolysis power-law model; NIH is the primary COU QoI. Clinical threshold (NIH < 0.01 g/100 L) is directly traceable to ISO 10993-4 haemocompatibility requirements for Class III devices. All validation QoIs are therefore directly relevant to the COU decision."
