        "description": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the same pump geometry (or a geometrically similar analogue with documented similarity parameters) at operating conditions within the COU operating envelope. At least 3 of the 5 COU operating points must be directly validated."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the identical geometry used in the COU. All five COU operating points (2, 3.5, 5, 6.5, 8 L/min at 3000–5000 RPM) are directly covered by bench validation. No geometric scaling or similarity arguments are required. Experimental facility (FDA CDRH hemolysis test rig) is the reference standard for this device class."
