        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residual levels < 1×10⁻⁵ for all transport equations. Mass imbalance must be < 0.01% of inlet mass flow. Solver settings (relaxation factors, numerical schemes) must be documented and shown to produce consistent results across operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "All steady-state RANS solutions converged to residuals < 5×10⁻⁶ for continuity, momentum, and k-ω equations. Mass imbalance < 0.003% at all five operating points. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Solver settings (second-order upwind for momentum, SIMPLE pressure-velocity coupling) documented in simulation record SR-COU2-2024. Convergence plots archived in simulation data package."
