        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The choice of turbulence closure (k-ω SST) and hemolysis correlation (Giersiepen–Wurzinger power law) must be justified by literature evidence and sensitivity analysis. Alternative model forms must be evaluated and documented. Model form uncertainty must be estimated and included in the total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "k-ω SST selected based on systematic comparison study (Jones et al. 2022, J. Biomech. Eng.) demonstrating superior WSS prediction in rotating blood-contacting devices versus k-ε and Spalart-Allmaras. Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis correlation validated for this shear-exposure regime (Arora et al. 2004). Model form uncertainty estimated at ±22% on NIH via ensemble of three turbulence models; included in total UQ budget. Sensitivity analysis confirmed k-ω SST as lowest-bias closure for this geometry."
    },
    {
