        "description": "Blood analogue fluid must be characterised per ASTM F1841. Pump specimens used for validation must be from the same manufacturing lot as the COU device or be dimensionally verified against the nominal CAD geometry within ±0.1 mm."
      },
      "rationale": "Glycerol-water blood analogue prepared and characterised per ASTM F1841; viscosity and density confirmed within specification. Pump specimen for validation is the FDA reference geometry machined to ±0.03 mm tolerance (CMM report CMM-2023-FDA-PUMP-001). Dimensional verification confirms all critical passages (gap widths, blade angles) within ±0.05 mm of nominal CAD. Three replicate test samples used; inter-sample NIH variability < 4%."
