      },
      "rationale": "Parameter equivalency matrix (PEM-COU2-v1.0) documents CFD vs. experimental values for all 14 input parameters. Maximum discrepancy: inlet turbulence intensity 4.2% (measured) vs. 4.0% (CFD) — sensitivity analysis shows < 0.8% effect on NIH. Fluid viscosity: 3.48 mPa·s (measured) vs. 3.50 mPa·s (CFD nominal) — within measurement uncertainty. Rotational speed: ±2 RPM agreement between tachometer and CFD boundary condition. All discrepancies below acceptance threshold; no offset rationale required."
